A contractor "Niteworks"of Britisch MoD hacked personal information on 831 members of defence community.

Russian government hackers penetrated the computer network of the Democratic National Committee and gained access to the entire database of opposition research on GOP presidential candidate Donald Trump
The Monte Melkonian Cyber Army took down Azerbaijani servers

Turkish hackergroup's attacks shutdown Armenian government websites; The attacks by the hackerteam named "AslanNeferlerTim" (LionPrivatesTeam) caused blackouts on government websites including defense, energy, agriculture ministries' sites, in addition to various other government agencies.
The CyberJusticeTeam claimed responsibility for a massive data leak of the syrian government
Pro-ISIS Algerian-based TeamSystemDz defaced 88 websites from the US, France, Israel and the UK. In particular, it defaced several websites in Richland County.
The Anonymous-affiliated hackinggroup "GhostSquad" blocked the KKKKnights website for several hours via DDoS
The Anonymous-affiliated hacking group "Ghost Squad" defaced the "Black Lives Matter" webportal with "All Lives Matter" banners

Unit 42 has discovered a persistent attack campaign operating primarily in the Middle East dating back to at least mid-2016 which we have named MagicHound. This appears to be an attack campaign focused on espionage. Possibly related to Iranian state-sponsored RocketKittenGroup aka CobaltGypsy aka APT35.

A complex, targeted malware framework that, unlike a military-grade APT, is“ stitched together” with freeware utilities in order to spy on more than 500 government agencies and organizations worldwide.
Chinese hackers APT 15 spied on UK military contractors.

Not identified hacker(s) posted to the web a 1.4 gigabyte compressed bittorrent file that appears to contain personal data on 50 million Turkish citizens, including their names, addresses, parents 'firstnames, cities of birth, birthdates, and a national identifier number used by the Turkish government, all of which were verified as authentic by the Associated Press.
Anonymous together with Ghost Squad targeted with DDoS attacks many international banks, in protest aganist corruption
Anonymous hacked Government websites of North Carolina in protest against an "anti-LGBT" Bathroom Law

PhineasFisher attacked the Catalan police union, defaced it's website, plundered their webserver, published personal information about policeofficers and hijacked their Twitteraccount, to protest their past extremely questionable and likely criminal behavior. He recorded the attack and made it public as a tutorial video
GhostSquad conducted a DDoS attack on the Trump Hotel Collection website to target Trump’s hate mongering
Iran's cyber police claim Statistical Centre was attacked by hackers in three Arab countries, including Saudi Arabia
Hackers target Czech Republic gov’t sites over plans to block gambling domains
Anonymous leaked personal details of 5,000 Spanish cops online as a protest against the gag law
Espionage Campaign which is possibly linked to Operation Groundbait from 2015.
Pakistani Hackers Deface Websites for Seven Indian Embassies, One Police Station
Ghost Squad Hackers Announce #OpSilence, Month-Long Attacks on Mainstream Media
Anonymous Attacks Anti-White Movements in South Africa and Zimbabwe

A hacker going by the handle of  SkyNetCentral conducted as series of distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attack on the official website of Society of the MuslimBrothers or MuslimBrotherhood (Al-Ikhwanal-Muslimun in Arabic) forcing the website to go offline despite using CloudFlareDDoS protection service
Hackers down House Democrats' websites

Incident Name: Diplomats in EasternEurope bitten by a TurlaMosquito
Description: Evidence was found that Turla installers were exfiltrating information since at least July 2016. The targets are mainly consulates and embassies from different countries in Eastern Europe or the vicinity.
According to the firm ProofPoint, Chinese state-sponsored actors continues to spy on military and aerospace organizations in Russia and Belarus.

Incident Name: Voting Systems hacked in US states before elections
Description: Voters personal data was stolen from Election Authorities in Illinois and Arizona, but also other states. At least 200.000 persons affected. But "due to the ambiguous nature of the attack," the elections board warned, "we may never know the exact number of affected voters".
20 Russian government and military facilities alongside several defence contractors were targeted via a spear-phishing campaign with malware sent via email.

Incident Name: shad0ws3c vs. Paraguyan Secretary of National Emergency
Description: Hacktivist group leaks information from Paraguayan Secretary of National Emergency

Anonymous conducted a series of cyber attacks on the Zimbabwe government websites for #ZimShutDown2016 or #ShutDownZimbabwe, a protest movement in which citizens are protesting against the Robert Mugabe’s government who has been in power for last 36 years. Sites went offline for several hours.
The whistleblowing website WikiLeaks said it had suffered a "sustained attack" over the announcement of publication of documents of Turkey's political power structure and the country's leadership.
Philippines Government Websites Hit by Massive DDoS Attacks, China Suspected
Anonymous hacks a Brazilian Court for blocking WhatsApp.
Information screens on Vietnamese Airports were hacked to show anti-Chinese messages

Incident Name: North Korea attack on South Korean Military
Description: NorthKorea appears to have hacked SouthKorea's cybercommand in what could be the latest cyberattack against Seoul, the military here said Tuesday,

The World Anti-Doping Agency said on Tuesday that hackers stole confidential medical information about U.S. Olympic athletes and published it on the internet, blaming a Russian group for the attack. In 2018, the US and some of its allies attributed this attack to Russian GRU officers.

Incident Name: APT  3 vs. Hongkong Organizations and Government Agencies
Description: APT 3, a state-sponsored Chinese hacking group, accessed two networks of the HongKong-City-Government, as well as other targets since march 2016 (according to Symantec).
The israeli cyber-securityfirm Intsights hacked an ISIS forum and found information concerning future terrorist attacks

Anonymous conducted cyber attacks on the government websites forcing several of them to go offline. The targeted websites include the official website of the federal government for the 2016 Games (brasil2016.gov.br), Portal of the State Government of Rio de Janeiro (rj.gov.br), Ministry of sports (esporte.gov.br), Brazil Olympic Committee COB (cob.org.br) and the official website of the Rio 2016 Olympics (rio2016.com).
GhostSquad took down the website of the israelian primeminister
Armenian Hackers stole Bank Data of Azerbaijani Persons and leaked it
GhostSquad Hackers deface 12 Afghan Government websites
Anonymous attacked japanese sites in response to renewed dolphin hunting
Australia's first digital census website receives DDoS attacks and breaks down

Incident Name: DDOS attack on austrian central bank
Description: A turkish hacktivist group managed to overload the website of the austrian central bank via an DDOS-attack
Hacker attacks American Human Rights Council and 62 other websites calling for jihad
Indian Central Bureau of Investigation and Army officers were targeted by a phishing campaign, according to an Indian Cybersecurity Blog/Research-Entity.
RedHack leaks personal E-Mail accounts of Turkish Energy Minister and Erdogan's son-in-law Albayrak
SymantecCorp, a digital security company, says it has identified a sustained cyberspying campaign, likely state-sponsored, against Indian and Pakistani entities involved in regional security issues.
Attacks aimed at banks in Poland appear to be part of a bigger campaign targeting financial organizations around the world, and researchers have found some links to the threat actor known as Lazarus.
Hackers penetrated the networks of the Bradley Foundation and leaked data (additionally some fake data)
Indian government sites hacked and defaced with propaganda by pakistani hackers.

Ukrainian hackers CyberHunta leaked over a gigabyte of emails (2,300) of Kremlin official Vladislav Surkov (with plans to destabilise Ukraine). Ukrainian officials affirm authenticity of the documents while the Kremlin says it's fake and denies Surkov even using email.

Chairperson of Donetsk People's Republic pension fund reported an attack and blocking of the fund database, so that pension payments were suspended. DPR blaimed Ukrainian hackers, presumably related to advance poll in DPR
Syrian Cyberarmy hacks Belgian Media Sites.
US election agency breached and 100 credentials of voters stolen, hacker tried to sell the data

A wiper malware sharing similarities with Shamoon 2.0, but even stronger with past attacks of Newsbeef aka Newscaster aka CharmingKitten targeted Saudi Arabian Corporations and was even found in an Kaspersky Network in Europe.
Hacker leaks personal data of 34 Mio. Keralites from Kerala government’s civil supplies department website, after department fails to address security flaws in website
WikiLeaks hit with'targeted' cyberattack after publishing over 8,000 more DNC emails
The website of ScotlandYard was taken down by Anonymous in response to an arrest of people at an anti-capitalist protest

Mere hours after Donald Trump was declared victorious in the wake of the US elections, Kremlin-linked hacker group CozyBear(APT29) ,reportedly launched a wave of attacks on US-based targets. According to Washington-based cyber response firm Volexity, CozyBear hackers launched five different spear-phishing campaigns,"with a heavy focus on U.S.-based think tanks and non-governmental organizations (NGOs)".

A hacker calling himself vim products claimed to have taken down the webpages of several mayor Russian banks for "customers"who bought the DDoS attack because their disapproval about Russias interference in the US elections. The effected sites included the Moscow Exchange, the Bank of Moscow, Rosbank, and Alfa-Bank.

Likely Iranian State-sponsored hackers (Crowd strike) have conducted a series of destructive attacks on Saudi Arabia over the last two weeks, erasing data and wreaking havoc in the computerbanks of the agency running the country’s airports and hitting five additional targets.
Kaputskiy hacks into Italian government site and exposes 45,000 users' data
Kaputskiy Breaks into Indian Regional Council Server and exposes 17,000 users' data
Shad0wS3C Hacker Breaches Mexican Government Website and exposes sensitive user date
DDoS attack brought down the Internet connection of the EU Commission staff. No data leak, no sign so far related attacks such as hijacking.
Austrian Foreign Ministry suffered a DDoS attack leading to the shutdown of webpage. Turkish involvement due to Austrian position on EU membership suggested.
Kaputskiy hacks into Indian High Commissions in Ghana and Fiji and exposes credentials of 200 accounts
Hackers defaced Kuwaiti parliament website one lection day accusing MP of being an Iranian agent
San Francisco Metro and Buscompany Muni was hacked, bringing their payment systems down for several days.

Nearly 1 Million Telekom Routers (and several hundred thousands from other companies) were targeted in order to include them in a gigantic Botnet. The hack did not function properly and led to the internet disruption of the affected enduser's systems. An individual hacker from London called "Spiderman" was arrested as only responsible individual.

Hackers took control of an Israeli newschannel and broadcast the Muslim call to prayer followed by anti-Israel propaganda which lasted about 30 seconds before the connection was restored. The hack allegedly took place in protest of a controversial bill that limits the volume of the ‘Adhan’from mosques in Israel.

Incident Name: Kaputskiy vs. Slovak Chamber of Commerece
Description: Kaputskiy breaks into Slovak Chamber of Commerce and accesses and exposes data belonging to more than 4,000 users
Sources from the Energy Ministry claim that a major cyber-attack is the source of the widespread electricity cuts across Istanbul in december, according to reports in the Turkish media.

Incident Name: Red Alpha Team against Tibetan Targets
Description: Citizen Lab provides an in-dep th view into a phishing operation that ran for 1 19 months, and which targeted the Tibetan community. Recorded Future later linked this campaign to the so called Chinese state-backed group Red Alpha.
Bahamut attacked various targets (many linked to activists or governments) with specifically crafted phishing attacks and highly-sophisticated malware. The allegiance of the APT is still unknown
Kaputskiy hacks Venezuelan Army and exposes details of  3,000 accounts
Kaputskiy hacks into Ecuador National Assembly and exposes 550-600 accounts

In December 2016, almost exactly a year after the attacks on the ukrainian electrical grid, Russian hackers took down the payment system of the ukrainian ministry of finance, treasury and pensionfund.

Incident Name: Kaputskiy and Kasimierz hack into Argentinian Ministry of Industry
Description: Kaputskiy and Kasimierz hack into Argentinian Ministry of Industry  website and breach personaldata
Ukraine Defence Ministry website disrupted
Kaputskiy hacks into Russian Consulate department Russian National Visa Bureau websites in the Netherlands, steals and exposes user information
Individual hacker Cryptolulz breaks into the data base of the website of Russian embassy of Armenia and leaks data
Cryptolulz targets Russian and Italian governments websites and conducts a DDoS attack

Hackers struck an electric transmission station north of the city of Kiev, blacking out a portion of the Ukrainian capital equivalent to a fifth of its total power capacity. The outage lasted about an hour.

After the Single Internet Gateway was passed into a law, the websites of the National Security Agency and the Ministry of Defense and four other ministries became inaccessible, Anonymous also defaced Thai LA consulate and leaked data in protest of arrests related to OpSingleGateway.

Incident Name: Chinese Ministry of State Security campaign
Description: Two Chinese hackers working with the Ministry of State Security (MSS) were indicted for unauthorized access and data theft from a variety of victims.

Incident Name: UN International Civil Aviation Organization hack
Description: China-linked group Emissary Panda breached into computer systems of UN International Civil Aviation Organization and spread malware to foreign government websites.

Allegedly Russian hackers disrupted various websites a few days before and on election day (16th of october). The montenegrin leaders accuse russia of these hacks and supporting even the preparation of a coup.

Incident Name: Bulgaria presidential election and referendum hack
Description: Allegedly Russian hackers disrupted the websites of the bulgarian electoral commission, presidency and other government institutions in the course of the upcoming presidential elections and the referendum on 6th of novermber.

Chinese state-sponsored hacking group "Emissary Panda" compromised the network systems of an European drone company and a U.S. subsidiary of a French energy management company in order to steal information relevant to economic and military competition.
State-sponsored Chinese hacking group Naikon/APT 30 conducted long-term espionage campaign agaginst government entities and government-owned companies in South East Asia and Australia.

Incident Name: Kaputskiy vs. Russian Visa Centre in USA
Description: Kaputskiy hacks Russian Visa Centre in USA and accessed information of around 3000 individuals

Incident Name: Tick aka PLA Unit 61419 vs. Japanese Defense Companies
Description: Japanese law enforcement believes Tick is linked to the Chinese military and behind a broad cyber-espionage campaign that has breached more than 200 Japanese companies and organizations since at least 2016.

Incident Name: Covellite attack on US electric grid
Description: Covellite, a propably state-sponsored north Korean group tried to access networks of US-American and subsequently European and asian companies associated with the electrical grid.

APT35 (The Newscaster Team) compromising at least three U.S.-based companies, and performing reconnaissance at two other U.S. organizations and one non-U.S. company. At least one organization was likely compromised due to the attacker exploiting unpatched vulnerabilities in the Ektron CMS platform, which allowed them to upload web shell backdoors.
The NSA conducted a major hijacking operation against various asian targets
An unknown actor with direct ties to the Chinese government leveraged malware deposited by other threatactors, to gain access to high-level networks in various countries
The APT Lazarus hijacked south-Korean servers to run cryptocoin miners
The actor SunTeam, attributed to be North Korean, hacked the devices of northKorean defectors and of journalists in South Korea to access the saved data

Incident Name: Octopus infected Seas of Central Asia
Description: Octopus infected Seas of Central Asia
Fancy Bear leaked Mails of the Macron French Presidential Campaign with the goal of influencing the French elections
The threatactor Windshift (likely connected to the WhiteCompany and Bahamut) attacked some specific individuals with long-term social-engineering attacks. The goal was likely credential theft
North Korean Proxy Reaper expanded its focus on japanese and vietnamese targets, as well as companies from the Middle East.
MSS supported hackers have stolen sensitive data by different companies and research entities in the US, Europe and Korea in 2017, according to a 2020 indictment.
Anonymous hacks Thai Gov’t job portal; leaks a trove of data
Russia managed to hack into at least 4000 NATO soldiers’ personal smartphones to obtain military information.
A group of hackers traced to China are waging a sophisticated cyberespionage campaign against satellite operators, telecommunication companies and defense contractors in the US and Southeast Asia

Cyberspies working for or on behalf of China's government have broadened attacks against official and corporate targets in Vietnam at a time of raised tension over the South China Sea, cyber security company Fire Eye said.

Attackers, believed to work for a nationstate, used malware–called Triton–to infiltrate a safety system for operations in critical infrastructure organizations. After initial allegations towards Iran, Fireeye reported in 2018, that it is highly likely, that the state-owned Russian Science Institute CNIIHM developed the malware.

Incident Name: Pakistan vs. Indian Security Guard Website
Description: Hackers suspected to be affiliated with Pakistan attacked the website of the elite National Security Guard (NSG), defacing the homepage with a profanity laden message against Prime Minister Modi.

Incident Name: Indian Revenge: Ransomware against Pakistani Airports
Description: Indian hackers claimed to have infected three Pakistani Airports with ransomware, as a revenge action after the defacement of the Indian Security Guard Website.
The Russian APT Fancy Bear leaked E-Mails of UN Staff
Iranian PupyRAT Bites Middle Eastern Organizations, closely related or working on behalf of Magic Hound (Palo Alto) APT 35 (Mandiant) Cobalt Gypsy (Secure Works)RocketKitten (CrowdStrike)

Iran-based group Chafer remains highly active and is moving up the telecoms and transport supply chain to facilitate widescale surveillance of targets. One of the tools used by Chafer was the EternalBlue exploit that was previously deployed in the devastating WannaCry and Petya attacks.

Incident Name: Charming Kitten vs. Instagram and Telegram
Description: Talos Intelligence reports several attacks on users of Instagram and Telegram. The Attacker used greyware of these applications to gain access to private information about his victims.

The RANCOR APT  group has been targeting political entities in Singapore, Cambodia, and Thailand, and likely in other countries, using two previously unknown strain of malware. The two malware families were tracked as DDKONG and PLAINTEE. The group might be related to the Chinese-based group DragonOk.
The russia APT Turla attacked the German government, after Fancy Bear was the suspect at the beginning of the investigation.

"Operation PZChao" targets US and Asian organisations with cyber-attacks reminiscent of Iron Tiger - but this time with the ability to drop trojans, conduct espionage, and mine bitcoin. Researchers spectaculate that the same Chinese-based APT (APT27 aka Emissary Panda) as in the Iron Tiger operation takes part in the new project but this is not proven yet.
The British governement initiated a cybercampaign against ISIS disrupting all of its actions within the Internet. Through 2017 ISIS was strongly prohibited in sharing ist propaganda over the web.
Unknown state-sponsored actors hijacked parts of the DNS-Infrastructure, allowing them to phish credentials of middle-eastern foreign offices and energy provides, before accessing confidential data
APT28 continued lowlevel intelligence gathering action between 2017 and 2018
Singapore Reveals CyberAttack on Defense Ministry
Russian hackers targeted Pentagon workers with malware-laced Twitter messages

Researchers from Palo Alto Networks' Unit 42 reveal the details of Muddy Water, a campaign carried on by a politically-motivated actor targeting Middle Eastern nations. Reaqta links the campaign to Iran as the geographical origin.

McAfee Advanced Threat Research analysts have discovered a new operation targeting humanitarian aid organizations and using North Korean political topics as bait to lure victims into opening malicious Microsoft Word documents. The Analysts of McAfee have named this Operation Honeybee, based on the names of the malicious documents used in the attacks.
Norway’s security service says nine emailaccounts—including those belonging to the Labourparty, the foreign ministry and defenseministry—have been targeted by hackers belonging APT 29.
The website of 45 Committee, a PAC supporting President Donald Trump, is defaced.

Two security researchers reveal the details of a new campaign linked to Charming Kitten, a cyber espionage group linked to the Iranian Government using an unsophisticated strain of malware, dubbed MacDownloader, to steal credentials and other data from Mac computers.

Incident Name: Hackergroup linked to ISIS attacks NHS websites
Description: The Independent reveals that, over the past six weeks, six NHS websites were defaced showing grue some images of the conflict in Syria with the hashtags: #Op_Russiaand#save_aleppo.

Incident Name: Indian Cyber Army vs. Pakistani Embassy in Serbia
Description: Hackergroup "Indian Cyber Army" hacks website of Pakistani embassy in Serbia, leaves message.

Incident Name: Attack on govermental websites in Montenegro
Description: The websites of the Montenegrin government and several state institutions, as well as some pro-government media, are targeted with multiple cyberattacks (probably by the Russian state) started since February, 15th.

Incident Name: Black Hat Hackers leak Navy Data of India
Description: Bangladeshi Hacker group "Black Hat Hackers" extracts and leaks personal information of Indian Navy officials from government servers.
DDoS attack takes down Luxembourg government servers

The United States targeted North Korea’s military spy agency. The attack was a distributed denial of service (DDoS) campaign with an aim to flood North Korean spy agency’s servers with traffic, crippling its access to the internet.

Incident Name: Unknown hacker attacks Kansas department of Commerce
Description: A security breach in the Kansas Department of Commerce exposes millions of Social Security numbers from people across 10 states to hackers. Many other accounts are also attacked.
The hacker group DarkHydrusaka Copy Kittenaka LazyMeerkat in 2017 mainly hacked the governmental and educational sector of different Middle East countries. The hacks are mainly harvesting attacks.

Incident Name: Unknown group attacks Democratic Party in Pennsylvania (USA)
Description: The Pennsylvania Senate Democrats are hit by a ransomware attack that locks senators and employees out of their computer network.

Incident Name: Attack on various US progressive groups (probably by CozyBear)
Description: New reports reveal that Russian hackers are targeting U.S. progressive groups in a new wave of attacks. According to the report, at least a dozen groups have faced extortion attempts since the U.S. presidential election. The ransom demands are accompanied by samples of sensitive data in the hackers’ possession.
Malware researchers at Palo Alto Networks spot a new strain of ransomware, dubbed Ran Ran, that has been used in targeted attacks against government organizations in the Middle East.

Incident Name: Turkish hackers attack several Dutch websites
Description: Turkish hackergroups target a large number of Dutch websites after the political fallout between the Netherlands and Turkey over the weekend.

Incident Name: Canadian Statistics website got shut down by hackers
Description: The Canadian government confirms that the Statistics Canada website is hacked and taken offline for over two days. In the aftermath of the cyberattack parts of the Canada Revenue Agency's (CRA) site is also reportedly taken offline by authorities as a precaution.

Incident Name: Ransomware found in the systems of the Tweede Kamer(NLD)
Description: Ransomware is found on the computersystems of the Tweede Kamer, the lower house of Dutch parliament.
IAAF says medical records compromised by Fancy Bear hackinggroup
Britain First is hit by a massive hack that targeting its websites and Twitter accounts, and their YouTube channel.

Incident Name: Lazarus (NorthKorea) attacks endusers because of financial interests
Description: Focusing on financial interests (Bitcoin) the NorthKorean APT Lazarus ends false job recruitments to gain data from endusers.
Lazarus managed to hack into Yapizon, a South Korean cryptocurrency exchange in April 2017 and stole 3,816 Bitcoins valued at $5.3million.
APT28 targeted primarily NATO Countries as well as Ukraine (among others) in a spearphishing campaign.

Incident Name: Chinese hackers attack UK think tanks
Description: The Chinese -based APT 26 (aka Deep Panda) attacked several UK think tanks and gained access to information regarding the PC China.
Chinese government hackers infiltrated US navy contractors.

Incident Name: Leviathan aka TEMP.periscope aka APT 40 influences on the election in Cambodia
Description: Since they want them to win the Chinese-based APT 40 supports a Chinese-friendly party in the Cambodian elections. Fire Eye has examined a range of TEMP. Periscope activity revealing extensive interest in Cambodia's politics, with active compromises of multiple Cambodian entities related to the country’s electoralsystem. This includes compromises of Cambodian government entities charged with overseeing the elections, as well as the targeting of opposition figures.

Incident Name: Unknown hacker disrupts emergency sirens in Dallas
Description: A computer hack sets off all the emergency sirens in Dallas for about 90 minutes.

Incident Name: Unknown APT attacks Singapore government and universities
Description: Reports emerge that the two Singapore universities suffered APT (advanced persistent threat) attacks last month, with the attackers specifically targeting government and research data.

WannaCry is ransomware that infects Windows operating systems that have not been patched with a specific patch offered by Microsoft since March 2017, and encrypts certain userfiles on the computer. The program asks to pay a certain amount of money in the cryptocurrency Bitcoin, after an unused period of time the program threatens with dataloss. In 2018 the USA brought charges against a North Korean agent of APT Lazarus, who was also held responsible for the Sony Hack 2014.
Russian state-sponsored hackers managed to access secured parts of the German energy network
OceanLotus accessed networks of local SEA governments, to use the mass taging points against the local organisation ASEAN.In the same campaign attacks were started against local humanrights defenders
South Korean Bitcoin exchange Youbit suffered a large-scale security breach that led to the theft of one fifth of userfunds.

The world's largest consumer credit reporting agency Equifax which is located in the USA was attacked by a first unknown group of hackers. As a result the attackers were able to steal personal information (adresses, social insurance numbers etc.) of more than 143 Million clients. In February 2020, the US unsealed an indictment against four Chinese PLA officers and blamed them for committing the hacks.
Lebanon blames Israel for anti-Hezbollah telecoms hacking

Cyber reason reveals the details of Operation Cobalt Kitty, a campaign carried on by APT32, an advanced threatgroup that conducts targeted intrusions at large multi national businesses with interests in Vietnam.
A stolen Trump-Duterte transcript appears to be just one part of a larger hacking story
A Russia-linked hacking group was found to have launched a spear-phishing campaign against Montenegro after the country announced its decision to join NATO
A fake News and hacking campaign was launched against Qatar in the context of the ongoing crisis
Recorded Future discovered a new espionage campaign dubbed the"Red Alpha"APT  with Chinese origin. One part of it, the campaign"2017 hktechy"took place in 2017 against the Tibetan Community.

The Al-Jazeera Media Network was attacked by an unknown hacker group. The group disrupted and hijacked the system afterwards. Then the website sent pro-iranien and pro-israelian contents for a couple of hours.

Incident Name: Vigilance attacks the governmental site of Minnesota
Description: A hacker calling himself Vigilance hacks a database belonging to the Minnesota state government, and steals about 1,400 email addresses and passwords.

A hackergroup of ISIS defaced the mainsite of the Argentinian military. As a result the site contained a message which was warning Argentinia about the ISIS in their country. After 20 minutes the army took down the site.
Iran attacks 9,000 emailaccounts in UK parliament. Russia was initially blamed but investigators have traced the attack to the Tehran regime, TheTime scan reveal.

Incident Name: ISIS hacks the governor's office of Ohio(USA)
Description: Ohio Gov. John Kasich’s website is hacked ,appearing to show pro- ISIS propaganda. Ohio first lady Karen Kasich’s website, along with the Ohio Department of Rehabilitation and Corrections website, are also hacked.

Russia used an updated ransomware program to target Ukrainian infrastructure, including power companies, airports, and public transit. ESET linked it to the group Telebots, which evolved from Blackenergy and is held resonsible for the Industroyer/Crashoverride attacks against ukrainian powergrid in december 2016. The US and UK Governments attributed it to the Russian Military.
The Russian hacker group known as APT28, or Fancy Bear, has targeted victims via their connections to hacked hotel Wi-Fi networks.

Symantec has uncovered the operations of a threat actor named Leafminer that is targeting a broad list of government organizations and business verticals in various regions in the Middle East since at least early 2017. The group tends to adapt publicly available techniques and tools for their attacks and experiments with published proof-of-concept exploits. Leafminer attempts to infiltrate target networks through various means of intrusion: watering hole websites, vulnerability scans of network services on the internet, and brute-force/dictionary login attempts. The actor’s post-compromise toolkit suggests that the group is looking for email data, files, and database servers on compromised target systems.

Incident Name: National Australian University attacked by Chinese hackers
Description: China-based hackers have successfully infiltrated the IT systems at the Australian National University, potentially compromising the home of Australia's leading national security college and key defence research projects.

Incident Name: New Details about SpringDragon (APT  of China)
Description: KasperskyLab reveals the details of a new wave of attacks carried on by a long running APT  actor dubbed SpringDragon (also known as LotusBlossom).
In August anonymous hackers broke into Italy's 5-Star’s webplatform, called “Rousseau” and obtained secret data on ist members and donors.
Fraudulent mails with malicious code addressed to German media companies and organizations in the field of chemical weapons research
An unknown hacker group with the capabilities of a state-sponsored APT attacked several countries with espionage malware. Most of the targets were located in the MENA-region.

Incident Name: Democratic opponent of Rep .Dana Rohrbacher was attacked several times
Description: FBI agents in California and Washington, D.C. , have investigated a series of cyberattacks over the past year that targeted a Democratic opponent of Rep. Dana Rohrabacher (R-CA). Rohrabacher is a 15-term incumbent who is widely seen as the most pro-Russia and pro-Putin member of Congress and is as taunch supporter of President Trump.

The Chinese state-sponsored APT  Axiom or rather APT  17 conducted a multi-staged espionage campaign first against the Software Ccleaner, owned by Avast, and at a later stage against targets like Google etc.. Important: Axiom and APT  17 are named as one actor in the report but not so by other sources, as for example the THAI CERT Threat Group Cards.
The official website of the Government of Pakistan was hacked by anonymous hackers on Thursday, who posted the Indian national anthem and Independence Day greetings on the portal.
Hackers disrupted and shut down dozens of Venezuelan government and state-backed websites, pledging online support to a protest campaign against the country's leader, Nicolas Maduro.
The computer networks of Ukrposhta, the national postal service in Ukraine, have reportedly been disrupted by a two-day distributed-denial-of-service cyberattack.

The online hacktivist group Anonymous has claimed responsibility for carrying out a DDoS attack on the official website of Charlottesville, Virginia. The motive behind was to protest against an incident in which activists were hit while protesting against a group of white supremacists.
Researchers from Palo Alto Networks reveal the details of a new operation carried on by the North Korea-linked Lazarus Group against individuals involved with US Defense Contractors.

Incident Name: Russian ATP Turla attacks G-20 participants
Description: ProofPoint reveals that Turla (Russian APT) appears to be actively targeting G20 participants and those interested in its activities including policy makers, member nations and journalists.The analysis is based on the discovery of a new Java Script dropper for a backdoor called KopiLuwak that Turla has been known to use.

Using the "risings unim plant", the North-Korean Lazarus-Group hacked various organisations and institutions in different countries. These attacks helped the group to gain information about important infrastructure (finances,energy,transportetc.) and military.
Verrit, a political fact-checking site is DDoSed almost immediately after it was endorsed by Hillary Clinton.
Security Firm FireEye reveals that the Zero-day vulnerability CVE-2017-0199 in Microsoft Office was exploited by suspected nation state hackers to spread the FinSpy malware

Digital activists linked to the Anonymous collective have claimed responsibility for a wave of cyberattacks against a number of Spanish government websites, the constitutional court and the Royal House website as part of a pro-Catalonia protest campaign.
A Turkish hacker group has claimed responsibility for a cyber attack that has rendered the Danish Ministry of Immigration website inaccessible.
The north Korean APT Lazarus hacked an online casino and managed to steal an substantial part of the earnings of the casino
Actors tied to the Moroccan government accessed the phones of human rights defenders in Morrocco

Chinese cyberattackers allegedly crashed the website of the Hudson Institute as the think tank was about to host an event with a Chinese political dissident that the Chinese government considers to be a criminal.
NorthKorean Lazarus (SubgroupAPT38/Bluenoroff) hackinggroup is likely responsible for attempt to steal US$ 500,000 from FarEasternbank.
VPN Filter malware infected thousands of home and small business routers and network devices worldwide.

Incident Name: Hackers deceive facebook users with fake profiles
Description: Using fake profiles on facebook, a group (probably the Hezbollah) tried to convince end users, download a contagious messenger program. With the spy software the hackers were able to steal data from the private devices immediately. Their targets have been mostly located in Central/Eastern Europe and in the MiddleEast.

Incident Name: Chinese hackers attack think tanks and NGOs
Description: Crowd strike reveals the details of espionage-driven targeted attacks carried on by Chinese actors against four Western think tanks and an additional one on governmental organizations (NGOs).

Incident Name: EmissaryPanda (ChineseAPT ) attacks the Mongolian national datacenter
Description: According to Kaspersky’s latest research, the Chinese hacking group EmissaryPanda aka APT 27 aka LuckyMouse used watering hole-style attacks and spearphishing emails to breach specific employees of the Mongolian datacenter. After gaining individual access, they leveraged those accounts to gain additional control over the facility’s infrastructure.

Incident Name: Sandvines Spyware Injection into turkish network
Description: The network company Sandvines injected spyware in the turkish communication network and misused it to controll the showcase of ads

Incident Name: Sandvines Spyware Injection into egyptian network
Description: The network company Sandvines injected spyware in the egyptian communication network and misused it to control the showcase of ads and to mine cryptocurency

APT28 has recently dispatched several malware distribution campaigns that try to take advantage of a Flash zero-day vulnerability that Adobe patched earlier this week. According to US cyber-security firm Proofpoint, the one which first spotted these attacks, APT28 targeted abroad set of targets across Europe and in the US.

Two websites run by the Czech Statistical Office(CSU) were taken offline after a DDoS attack tried to disrupt reporting of the country’s parliamentary elections. According to the CSU, the vote count was not affected.

A threat actor launched a ransomware operation on networks in several countries, mainly in Russia. The operation is believed to have disrupted the Kiev metro system and the Odessa airport. In October 2018, the United Kingdom attributed this incident to Russian military intelligence GRU. But it seems contested, whether it was the work of Fancy Bear or Telebots (aka Sandworm).

Incident Name: APT34 aka Oilrig hacked unnamed Middle Eastern government entity
Description: Targeted Phishing Attack against a governmental entity in the middle east, which used a vulnerability which was released just days before.

Incident Name: Iranian hackers attacked the Austal company
Description: The Austal company was attacked by unknown hackers who stole shipdesigns, some staff email addresses and mobile phone numbers. Unlike the Australian CyberSecurity Centre (ACSC) the Australian Broadcasting Corporation (local media) claimed that Iranian hackers had executed the attack.

Hackers affiliated with the hacking group Akincila claimed responsibility for hijacking the Times of Israel and Asia Times websites on Thursday (2 November), replacing their main pages with images of children waving the Turkish flag.

A new APT, called "The WhiteCompany", later attributed as the same actoras the hacking for hiregroup Bahamut by Blackberry, attacked the Pakistan AirForce with spear-phishing messages that weaponized lurefiles with names referenced events, government documents, or newsarticles of interest for the targets.

Incident Name: Anonymous steals data from employees of the Italien government
Description: The Anonymous collective publishes some internal document stolen from the email accounts of some government employees.

The hacktivist collective Anonymous claims responsibility for taking down over a dozen neo-Nazi sites in retaliation for recent ongoing events in the US. These attacks are a part of the ongoing #OpDomesticTerrorism campaign.

Gallmaker is an attack group that is targeting government, military and defense targets in the Middle East and Eastern Europe. The group uses living off the land (LotL) tactics and publicly available hack tools to carry out activities that seems to be a cyber espionage campaign.

Incident Name: Anonymous attacks US and Israel government
Description: In name of #OpIsrael and #OpUSA, hacktivists from the Anonymous Collective leak online names, emails, and passwords of Israeli public employees and share a list of US government sites to target, calling on action against them.
In the "Zebrocy"-campaign the Russian-sponsored APT Fancy Bear aka APT28 aka Sofacy attacked various organisations of governments which are linked to foreign affairs.

The iranian government concucted an extensive surveillance program through the hacking group APT-C-50 on internal dissidents, oppositions forces, ISIS advocates, the Kurdish minority in Iran, and more.

Incident Name: Chinese Ministry of State Security campaign
Description: Two Chinese hackers working with the Ministry of State Security (MSS) were indicted for unauthorized access and data theft from a variety of victims.
Chinese state hacked into websites, which are mostly used by uyghurs, in order to hack into Apple, Google, and Windows phones.
The hacking group Patchwork/ Dropping Elephant conducted an espionage campaign on China and other states in order to gain sensitive information.
The network systems of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) were breached and approximately 500 MB of data related to Mars missions stolen.
Allegedly Chinese state-backed hackers used a new malware, named KHRAT, in order to compromise the networks systems of the cambodian government.

Name Initiator II: Rana Company/Ministry of Intelligence and Security
Description: U.S. authorities detected an Iranian state surveillance campaign on Iranian citizens, especially dissidents and others, conducted by the front company Rana.

Incident Name: Chinese hackers gain access to classified data of the US-Navy
Description: Chinese government hackers have compromised the computers of a Navy contractor, stealing 600+ Gb of highly sensitive data related to undersea warfare, including secret plans to develop a supersonic anti -ship missile for us on U.S. submarines by 2020, according to American officials. The attack occurred in January and February.

Roughly 30,000 DOD military and civilian personnel are believed to be affected by a cyberattack. A third-party contractor is compromised, granting the attackers access to the Pentagon network to steal travel data for DOD personnel.

Incident Name: Saudi-Arabia hacks the phones of its critics
Description: Omar Abdulaziz is a Canadian permanent resident and vocal critic of the Saudi government. The Saudi Arabian state used the pegasus spyware to gain access to Abdulaziz's phone. Once a phone is infected, the customer has full access to a victim’s personalfiles, such as chats, emails, and photos.They can even surreptitiously use the phone’s microphones and cameras to view and eavesdrop on their targets. The hack was allegedly used to even spy on Jamal Khashoggi in the months before his murder. Ghanem al-Masarir and Yahya Assiri, two Saudi Arabian human rights activists living in exile, were even targeted by the spyware.

Incident Name: Midterm Elections-Attack on the Republican Party
Description: Shortly before the Midterm Elections an election campaign comittee of the Republican Party was hacked by an unknown attacker group. Espionaging the e-mail accounts of four highranked employees the attackers gained access to thousands of e-mails.

Incident Name: Red Alpha Team Operation "2018 internet docss"
Description: Recorded Future discovered a new espionage campaign dubbed the"Red Alpha"APT  with Chinese origin. One part of it, the campaign" 2018 internet docss"took place in 2018 against the Tibetan Community.
According to unnamed experts, probably the Chinese APT 10 spied on Airbus in 2018.
The Russian espionage group Waterbug hijacked the infrastructure of an iranian state-sponsored hacking group in order to spy on targets worldwide.
The South Korean Resettlement Agency was hacked, and some hundred sets of personal data of North Korean refugees were leaked
Unknown Actors infected computers of the qatari foreign office with malware, via an Adobe zero-day
Congressman Broidy was hacked by allegedly qatarian actors, accessing his E-Mail account and leaking the data to American media
The iranian group Mabna Institutes proofed websites, and managed to access credentials of various educational institutions worldwide
The APT StealthFalcon gained access to various-not further specified networks around the middle eastern region, via an Windows Zero-Day-Vulnerability
The ukrainian cyber-command warned of an increasing number of new malware infections by Russian-aligned Gamaredon APTvs. Ukraine during KerchCrisis
The North-Korean APT Lazarus accessed indian ATMs
Various south- and southeastasian NGOs were compromised by the Chinese threat actor Bronze President
Amnesty revealed a sophisticated phishing campaign against various Humanright defenders across the middle east
The APT StrongPity spied on turkish citizens, highly likely with a connection to the conflict between Turkey and the Kurds

Singapore's largest healthcare group, SingHealth, reveals to have suffered a cyberattack to a company database in which attackers copied information belonging to roughly 1.5 million patients, including the country's primeminster, Lee Hsien Loong. The attack was discovered on July 4 and all patients who visited the clinics from May 1, 2015 through July 4, 2018 were affected.
Taiwan attributed an "omnipresent" espionage campaign against their government institutions to the Chinese state-sponsored APT s BlackTech and Taidoor
According to people with knowledge into the matter, the FiveEyes alliance gained access to Russian Yandex in 2018.
MSS supported hackers have stolen sensitive data by different companies in the US in 2018, according to a 2020 indictment.

Incident Name: Twitter account of Syed Akbaruddin hacked
Description: The verified Twitter account of Syed Akbaruddin, India 'stop diplomat to the United Nations, is briefly taken over by suspected Turkish hackers (AyyıldızTim).

Incident Name: Fox News Hosts and Trump-supporting Ex-sheriffs Twitter Accounts defaced
Description: The twitter page of two foxnews hosts was taken over by turkish hacktivists and their personal data leaked there

Researchers from Palo Alto Networks Unit 42 uncover Gorgon, a threatactor allegedly operating from Pakistan and targeting governmental organizations in the United Kingdom, Spain, Russia, and the United States leveraging spearphishing emails with Microsoft Word documents exploiting CVE-2017-0199.

Incident Name: The AnonPlus group hacked the Florence branch of the PD
Description: The AnonPlus hacker group says they have hacked the Florence branch of the Italian centre-left Democratic Party (PD) and leaked data regarding leader Matteo Renzi online.

Pyeongchang Winter Olympics organizers confirm that the Games had fallen victim to a cyberattack during Friday’s opening ceremony, but they refused to reveal the source. Researchers from CiscoTalos call the malware OlympicDestroyer and confirm that the only purpose is to disrupt systems. The hackergroup, called Hades by Kaspersky, used techniques to make it look like Lazarus has been responsible. Later on, unnamed US officials from the intelligence branch said that the Russians tateled APTS and worm has been the likely culprit.

Incident Name: Campaign Desert Scorpion, allegedly tied to Operation Frozen Cell (2016-2017) --> APT-C-23
Description: Researchers from Lookout reveal the details of an espionage campaign using two malware strains called Desert Scorpion and FrozenCell, to spy on targets in Palestine. The attackers are thought to be linked to Hamas.

Incident Name: Hackers successfully infiltrated the election campaign computer of David Min
Description: Reuters reveals that the U.S. Federal Bureau of Investigation is investigating a cyberattack on the congressional campaign of David Min, a Democratic candidate in California.

Incident Name: LuckyMouse APT  aka Emissary Panda aka APT 27
Description: KasperskyLab discovers several infections from a previously unknown Trojan, likely related to the infamous Chinese-speaking threat actor–LuckyMouse. The most peculiar trait of this malware is its driver, signed with a legitimate digital certificate.
The iranian APT FoxKittens hacks into government and private networks in the US and commercial targets worldwide.

The aggressive phishing campaign of Lazarus, executed on Mar.2 and 3, targeted a major government-controlled financial organization, a second government body involved in finance and trade, and three other large financial institutions. All targets are located in Turkey. Later on, Mcafee expanded the targets list regarding numerous sectors worldwide.

Incident Name: Anonymous publishes 26 thousand email addresses of italian teachers
Description: The Italian branch of the Anonymous collective leaks from the Italian Ministry of Education, 26,000 emails of teachers belonging to all level of schools. They also leak 200 administrative staff addresses.
Lazarus attacked various cooperate entities across Germany, Poland, Turkey, India, Japan and the ROK with its new insertion framework MATA

In name of Op Israel, more than a dozen major Israeli websites, belonging to hospitals, local authorities, the Israeli Opera, Israel Teachers Union and the IDF Widows and Orphans Organization are defaced apparently in response to clashes between the IDF and Gazan protesters the previous weekend.

Incident Name: Hackers use vulnerability of Cisco switches
Description: The Iranian IT Ministry reveals that Hackers have attacked networks in a number of countries including datacenters in Iran where they left the image of a U.S. flag on screens along with a warning: “Don’t mess with our elections”. The attack, exploiting CVE-2018-0171, affected 200,000 router switches across the world in a widespread attack, including 3,500 switches in Iran.

Incident Name: Team Kerala CyberWarriors attack websites in Pakistan
Description: Team Kerala CyberWarriors, a hacking group based out of India, begin to install ransomware on websites based out of Pakistan. The ransomware is called KCW Ransomware.

Incident Name: Greek & Turkishhackers target each other’s mediaoutlets
Description: The Turkish hacker group Akincilar ("Invaders") starts its offensive against Greece and defaces four websites(Greek Foreign Ministry, Athens-Macedonia News Agency-ANA-, the Greek Handball Federation, and Suzuki-Greece) in response to Athens'refusal to hand over the Turkish officers who fled to Greece in July 2016. As a retaliation for the attacks of the Turkish collective Akincilar, Greekhackers from Anonymous paralyze the 24TV Livewebsite for several hours. They also claim to have hacked 12,987 routers of TurkTelekom.
The Tennessee county's website is taken down by a DDoS attack on election night.

Incident Name: Russian-based APT(?)Hades attacks targets in Ukraine, Europe and Russia
Description: According to telemetry and the characteristics of the analyzed spear-phishing documents, Kaspersky believes the attackers from Olympic Destroyer are now targeting financial organizations in Russia, and biological and chemical threat prevention laboratories in Europe and Ukraine.

Researchers from Palo Alto Networks Unit 42 reveal to have detected multiple attacks by the OilRig group appearing to originate from a government agency in the Middle East. The attacks delivered a PowerShell backdoor called QUADAGENT.
The Phone of Jeff Bezos was hacked by hackers attributed to be directly connected to the Saudi-Arabian prince

A group of vigilante hackers going by SB315 deface some Georgia sites and threaten retaliation if a planned bill becomes law. The list of the targets include: the City of Augusta (that denies the hack), the website of Calvary Baptist Church, Georgia Southern University, the sites for two Augusta restaurants, BlueSkyKitchen and SoyNoodleHouse.
Turkish hackers from Akincilar launch a new cyberattack against Honda Greece. The automaker’s website in Greece is infiltrated with a message condemning the country for “partnering” with terrorists.

Incident Name: Anonymous defaces website of Russia’s Federal Agency for International Cooperation (Rossotrudnichestvo)
Description: The hacker group Anonymous defaced several subdomains of the official website of Russia’s Federal Agency for International Cooperation (Rossotrudnichestvo) against the ongoing censorship in the country, especially the recent ban on Telegram.

Incident Name: Attack on Russian Central Election Commission
Description: The Russian Central Election Commission was hit by a DDoS attack "from 15 different countries".

Incident Name: City of Atlanta was hit by a Sam Sam Ransomware
Description: IT systems used by the City of Atlanta, are hit by a Sam Sam ransomware attack, cutting off some online city services and potentially putting the personal information of employees and citizens at risk.

Incident Name: Anonymous defaces screens at the Mashhad airport
Description: Anonymous defaced the screens at the Mashhad airport in Iran to protest against the Government and the military’s activities in the Middle East.
The APT Chafer Attacked primarily Kuwaiti Networks between May 2018 and July 2019
South Korean cryptocurrency exchange Bithumb says that 35 billion won ($31.5 million) worth of virtual coins have been stolen by the NorthKorean APT Lazarus.

Incident Name: Andariel Group attacks website of South Korean non-profit organisation
Description: Researchers from Trend Micro discover a new campaign from the Andariel Group carried out via the injection of a malicious script into four compromised South Korean websites for reconnaissance purposes.
A criminal hacker managed to access secure data files of the US military via an unpatched network gap
Barium inserted backdoors into automatic updates for ASUS lAPT ops. The vulnerability was active for about 5 Months.

Shares in the Bank of Chile are down after it confirms hackers siphon off $10 million of its funds, mainly to Hong Kong. However the bank says no client accounts have been impacted. Apparently a wiper malware was used to conceal the real purpose of the attack.

Incident Name: DDoS-attack on the website of the Mexican National Action Party
Description: The website of the Mexican National Action Party is hit by a cyberattack during the final television debate between presidential candidates ahead of the July 1 vote, after the site had published documents critical of the leading candidate.

Incident Name: Andariel (Subgroup of Lazarus) attacks South Korean think tank
Description: According to researchers at AlienVault, North Korea-linked hackers planted an ActiveX zero-day vulnerability on the website of a South Korean think tank focused on national security.

Incident Name: TEMP. Periscope aka APT 40 aka Leviathan targeted UK-based engineering company
Description: Researchers from RecordedFuture rereveal the details of a spearphishing campaign carried out by the Chinese TEMP.Periscope group against a UK-based engineering company, leveraging Russian APT  Techniques. The Group is normally tied to the Chinese state, by Fireeye and IntrusionTruth.

In July 2018, Unit 42 analyzed a targeted attack using a novelfile type against at least one government agency in the Middle East. It was carried out by a previously unpublished threat group they trackas DarkHydrus.

Incident Name: Hamas (probably) hacks mobilephones of isralian soldiers
Description: 100 Isralian soldiers became victims to different apps of the google playstore. The apps which seemed to be completely normal were infected by malware spying on all activities on the soldiers smartphones. The Reuter Agency asserted that the terror organisation Hamas started the attack.
The cellphone of Ehud Barak was hacked-apparently without negligence on the part of the former israelian prime minister

Incident Name: Chinese hackers defaced the official website of the Taiwanese DDP
Description: The Democratic Progressive Party's (DPP) official website is defaced by Chinese hackers and the website is replaced with pictures and words reading "Chinese netizens are supporting TsaiIng-went or un for re-election" in simplified Chinese characters.
Security researchers from the Z-LabatCSE Cybersec reveal the details of Operation"Roman Holiday"an operation carried on by APT28 (AKA Fancy Bear)and targeting the Italian Military.

Incident Name: Tinder profile of RAF airwoman got hacked
Description: An RAF airwoman hasher Tinder profile hacked.The attackers use the hacked profile to steal secrets of Britain’s new F-35 Lightning II stealthfighter.
State-sponsored PRK -hackers stole 13.5 Million US-Dollars from the indian cosmosbank

Incident Name: Anonymous Catalonia defaces the website of the Banco de España
Description: Hacktivists from Anonymous Catalonia claim to have taken down the website of Banco de España.

Incident Name: Iranian APT Chafer focuses on diplomatic entities in the Middle East
Description: Throughout the autumn of 2018 Kaspersky analyzed a long-standing cyber-espionage campaign that was primarily targeting foreign diplomatic entities based in Iran. The attackers were using an improved version of Remexi in what the victimology suggests might be a domestic cyber-espionage operation. This malware has previously been associated with an Iranian APT actor that is widely called Chafer.
The iranian actor Seedworm hacked various firms, primarily related to telecommunication with the goal of datatheft. The exact origin of this group remains unknown

Incident Name: US State Department breached by unknown hacker(s)
Description: The State Department suffers a breach of its unclassified emailsystem, and the compromise exposes the personal information of a small number of employees.

Incident Name: Turkish hacking group attacked Egypt's state-run newsagency
Description: A Turkish hacking group have taken over the website of Egypt's state-run newsagency to condemn deathsentences against leaders of the blacklisted Muslim Brotherhood movement.
A DDoS attack takes down California Democratic Bryan Caforio’s website just hours before he steps onto the debate stage to face fellow Democrats.
An unknown hackergroup attacked Facebook and stole data of 50 Million of its users. The attackers gained access by using three different weaknesses of the company`s system.

Incident Name: Fancy Bear attacks European and US targets ("Cannon"Malware)
Description: Researchers from PaloAlto Networks reveal the details of a new campaign carried out by the infamous APT28, AKA Fancy Bear, AKA Sofacy, via the Cannon malware.
Researchers from ESET discover a new wateringhole campaign targeting 21 distinct websites in Southeast Asia carried out by OceanLotus.

Roughly 30,000 DOD military and civilian personnel are believed to be affected by a cyberattack. A third-party contractor is compromised, granting the attackers access to the Pentagon network to steal travel data for DOD personnel.
The website of Peter King was hacked and defaced by Turkish Hacktivists

Incident Name: Defacement of the website of the Bhartiya Janata Party’s Goawing
Description: The website of the Bhartiya Janata Party’s Goawing was defaced on Monday, 15 October during the day.
The website of the Saudi Arabian investment conference, referred to as“Davos in the Desert”, is defaced with anti-Saudi messages, to protest against the death of journalist Jamal Khashoggi.

Incident Name: Carbanak  vs. Ukraine during Kerch Crisis
Description: Russian state-sponsored actors phished access to various ukrainian and eastern European government institutions

Incident Name: Anonymous took down several Gabon websites
Description: The hacktivist group Anonymous takes down 70 Gabon government websites as part of its “anti-dictatorships” campaign.
In name of #AntiSecITA, hackers from the Anonymous collective`s wing in Italy hacked several university sites.
Security researchers at Trend Micro discover a PowerShell-based backdoor, active in Turkey, which resembles a malware used by Muddy Water threat actor.

Incident Name: US Attack on Internet Reseach Internet Agency
Description: The US Cyber command managed to shut down the infamous Russian influence agency "Internet research Agency"

Incident Name: APT29s first attack after one year of silence
Description: Multiple security companies including Crowdstrike and FireEye reveal a new spear phishing campaign carried out by APT29 (after one year of silence) targeting multiple sectors in the U.S.

Incident Name: The Digital Revolution group hacks the Kvant Scientific Research Institute
Description: The Russian Digital Revolution group claims to have hacked the servers of Moscow-based Kvant Scientific Research Institute, and gathered evidence of a neural networks tool used to analyze activities on social networks.

The servers of the remote access tool Citrix were hacked, and important data (highly likely passwords) were stolen. The perpetrator is at this point still unclear, but might have been an Iranian state hacker group.
Mikroceen was used by a Chinese actor (likely ViciousPanda) against central asian government agencies

Incident Name: Fancy Bear vs. US Energy Sector
Description: Fancy Bear started a long term espionage campaign against the US energy sector and political targets, accessing data and secure networks

Oil companies in Europe and the Gulfare hit by a new version of the Shamoon malware. The attacks started in India and hit the servers in Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates and Kuwait. Fingers are pointed to Iran.

Incident Name: Charming Kitten vs. US and Arab Officials
Description: Hackers believed to be associated with Charming Kitten (Iran-based APT) has ramped up their activities with a phishing campaign against American officials charged with enforcing economic sanctions imposed on Iran by President Trump.

A report by Area 1 Security reveals that a successful phishing attack on the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Cyprus, an EU member nation, compromised the diplomatic communication network for the European Union (COREU).
Iranish actors hacked various UK companies and the UK postoffice
The news sites of Bulatlat, Kodao and Pinoy Weekly are taken down by a DDoS attack, after stories on the Communist Party of the Philippines’ 50th anniversary were posted.

Incident Name: Italian Trade Union of State Police Officers Hacked & Defaced by The Anonymous Anarchist Agency
Description: Hackers from the Anonymous collective release the contact information of over 200 Italian police officers, including their full names and personal emailaddresses. Hackers also post the user loginname and password of 26 website administrators.

Incident Name: NSO-campaign focusing on Amnesty International in Saudi-Arabia
Description: In June 2018, an Amnesty International staff member received a malicious WhatsApp message with Saudi Arabia-related bait content and carrying links Amnesty International believes are used to distribute and deploy sophisticated mobile spyware.

Incident Name: Greek & Turkish hackers target each other’s mediaoutlets
Description: As a retaliation for the attacks of the Turkish collective Akincilar, Greekhackers from Anonymous paralyze the 24TV Livewebsite for several hours. They also claim to have hacked 12,987 routers of TurkTelekom.

Incident Name: Chinese Ministry of State Security campaign
Description: Two Chinese hackers working with the Ministry of State Security (MSS) were indicted for unauthorized access and data theft from a variety of victims.

Incident Name: Breach and data theft from South Korea's Defense Ministry
Description: Hackers breach 30 computers of South Koreas Defense Ministry and steal data from 10 of them.
Alleged state-sponsored turkish hackers breached into computer systems of at least 30 organizations across Europe and the Middle East in an extensive DNS hack campaign.
China-based hacking group "Chimera" compromised the networks systems of seven semiconductor companies in Taiwan.

Lookout Security Intelligence discovered an espionage campaign of a pakistani group, probably members of the military, on government officials and civilians in Pakistan, Afghanistan, india, Iraq, Iran, and the UAE.
The hacking group BITTER gained access into governemental and commercial entities in Pakistan and Saudi Arabia.

The state-sponsored Vietnamese hacking group "OceanLotus" conducted an espionage campaign on the vietnamese activist Bui Thanh Hieu in Germany, the organization Vietnamese Overseas Intitative for Conscience Empowerment (VOICE) in the Phillipines and an unnamed activist in Vietnam.
The algerian hacking group "North African Fox" targets military entities in Arab countries.
The Chinese threatactor Rancor accessed cambodian government networks via an spearphishing campaign
Chinese state-sponsored hacker group "Winnti" breached into computer systems of German pharmaceutical company Bayer, according to the company no data was stolen.
Chinese hacking group gained access into more than 200 network systems of government entities in Southeast Asia.
Iran-linked hacking group APT39/Chafer targeted the computer systems of kuwaiti government and air transportation.
North Korean state-sponsored hackers compromised the network systems of south Korean targets with a remote access trojan called "NavRAT" in order to steal information.
The north Korean state-sponsored hacking group "Lazarus Group" gained access into the network systems of the chilean company Redbanc, which interconnects the ATM infrastructure of all Chilean banks.
Korean hacking group Dark Hotel utilized an Internet Explorer vulnerability to target companies in South Korea and Japan.

The hack-for-hire group "Bahamut" is behind a variety of campaigns, including malicious applications, fake news and phishing campaigns in order to access network systems and steal data with targets in South Asia and the Persian Gulf.
Via watering hole techniques the SEA managed to disrupt the service of the IS news-website "Al Swarm"
Chinese state-sponsored group APT 31/Zirconium gained access into the IT network systems of the norwegian government and stole data.

Chinese state-sponsored group APT 31/Zirconium gained access into the IT network systems of the norwegian software firm Visma and stole data. In 2019, Recorded Future attributed the same operation to Chinese APT  10.
The hacking group "BITTER" targeted Chinese military industry personel with the malware called SlideRat.
Russian Hackers, attributed by the ukrainian government to be part of the Russian state, took down the infrastructure of the ukrainian electoral commission.
Over the course of the summer of 2019 hackers alleged to be Iranian government supported accessed various important parts of the Bahrainian state networks
The American military managed to shut down a database of Iran, which was used to target oil tankers
Hamas-affiliated Hacktivists created backdoors in the networks of israelian companies, to use them in the OpIsrael 2019 event
The vietnamese state-sponsored group Ocean Lotus/APT32 managed to hack 5-10 car manufacturers globally via freely available tools
Unknown actors took down almost the complete network of the US-American city of Baltimore. Links to the NSA software EternalBlue that was leaked on the internet remain inconclusive
The unidentified group 0v1ru$ managed to access important data of the Russian FSB
The United States attacked the Iran after the physical attacks of Iran on the Saudi oil facilities. The strike was focused on reducing the propaganda capabilities of the Iran

A spyware designed by the Israeli firm NSO group was used against various high-ranking government and military officials in countries allied to the US. Detailed attribution is unclear, but NSO says it only sells its software to governments
The networks of various US cities were temporarily taken down by ransomware of Russian origin

The iranian state-sponsored APT33 hacks primarily Saudi targets, but also in India and other targets, using changed infrastructure since the latest publication of their operations in March 2019 by Recorded Future.
The Russian state-sponsored APT Gamaredon started with attacks on various targets in the Ukraine, partly with the goal of data theft, partly with the goal of increasing its offensive capabilities.

Incident Name: Ryuk usage against US coast guard
Description: The networks of an US-American port authority was taken down by cybercriminals via the ryuk malware
The ukrainian gas company Burisman was attacked by Fancy Bear. Supposedly to find information about Joe Biden.

Unkown actors, attributed by unknown officials allegedly Chinese, hacked into the systems of the Australian Parliament three months ahead of elections, raised fears of election interference, but no leaked data became public.
The north-Korean APT attacked Russian companies with previously used tools
In Summer 2019 the Russian APT Fancy Bear attacked various embassies of Eastern European and Central Asian countries.
The hongkong part of amnesty international was the target of an attack by a Chinese APT .
The Chinese government accessed the networks of telecommunication providers in various countries to get data about the travel routes of Uighurs.
An attack on the messenger service telegram took down the service for a couple of hours. The attack was linked to a Chinese state hacker group.
APT  40 attacked American universities via spearphishing. The apparent goal was the theft of crucial information about naval research.
The threat actor Thrip continues its attacks around South East Asia. The targets are mostly military entities and satellite providers
The phone of Netanyahus Challenger Benny Gantz was hacked, the stolen data was allegedly sold to Iranian state actors.
The APT Cloud Atlas continued its campaigns against government institutions and companies across Russia, Eastern Europe and Central Asia
The Iranian State APT Charming Kitten restarted attack campaigns against Iranian dissidents and started to influence elections

Incident Name: National Association of Manufacturers vs. Chinese Hackers
Description: Hackers of Chinese origin attacked the networks of the American National association of Manufacturers during the talks about trade between the US and China
Many sectors in Kazakhstan were surveilled and hacked by the threat actor Golden Falcon, which may be linked to the Kazakh government.
On the 28th October 2019 many websites in Georgia were taken down by an coordinated attack. The US and many of its allies attributed this to Sandworm
Czech Authorities blame the GRU`s Fancy bear for a DDoS-Attack against the Czech Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
A private company directly connected to the UAE government developed and distributed a messenger app designed to conduct surveillance against UAE citizens.
The Chinese government DDOSed the Hongkong-Website LIHKG via a man-in-the-middle-attack, injecting malicious webcode in javascript-scripts on certain webpages.

Incident Name: Dtrack vs. Indian nuclear power plant
Description: Dtrack-Malware, associated with North Korean Lazarus group, was inserted into an Indian nuclear power plant.
Iranian state-backed hackers attacked the Bahrainian Oil-Company Bapco with a data-wiping malware
Lazarus continued its attacks against unnamed actors in the cryptocurrency sector
North Korean attackers accessed the networks of an unidentified American government agency
Charming Kitten tried to gain information about academics and their accounts by impersonating as journalists
The APT  Winnti installed Keyloggers on the computers of universities in Hongkong
Turla created a watering hole, with which they managed to compromise various Armenian web pages
The state-attributed APT DarkHotel used 5 Zero-Days over the course of 2019 to spy on North Korea
The threat actor Naikon reemerged in 2019 and 2020 with a new attack wave on governments in SEA and Australia.
APT34 attacked middle-eastern oil companies with its new file-deleting malware ZeroCleare

A group (likely the north-Korean APT Lazarus) attacked two central European defense companies via LinkedIn with the goal of espionage. In one case, the attackers tried to monetize access to a victim’s email account through a business email compromise (BEC) attack as the final stage of the operation.
Spyware of the NSO group was used against a Morrocan journalist by the Morrocan government.
The unidentified group Shadow Brokers leaked hackingtools of the Iranian group OilRig online

Incident Name: Togo NSO tools vs. Religious opposition
Description: The government of Togo used spyware tools of the NSO group against the religious opposition in the country

Since June 2019, unidentified cyber actors have used a SharePoint vulnerability, CVE-2019-0604, to exploit notable US entities. Following a widespread scanning for CVE-2019-0604 in May, June, and October 2019, respectively, cyber actors compromised the network of two identified US municipalities using CVE-2019-0604.

Incident Name: Emissary Panda attack on Iranian and other Middle Eastern Governments
Description: Chinese cyber-espionage group Emissary Panda has been targeting government organizations in two different countries in the Middle East, Palo Alto Networks security researchers say. Iran later claimed to be one of the victims and attributed the operation to Chinese APT 27.
An Indian hacker group named "I Team Crew" disrupted many pakistani websites after an suicide attack of pakistan-based group Jaish-e-Mohammad in Kashmir, which killed 40 police officers.
US Cyber Command disrupts iranian missile control systems and spy network to retaliate the downing of a US Global Hawk Drone and the attack on two oil tankers in June 2019.
China-linked hacking group "Tick" breached into computer systems of Mitsubishi Electric Corporation and stole sensitive data.
A probably state-linked hacking group compromised the computer systems of the UN offices in Geneva and Vienna, which the UN tried to cover up.
Suspected iranian hacking group "Greenbug" targets telecom providers in South Asia.

Incident Name: Russia interference in Britains general election 2019
Description: Russian hacking group stole U.S.-UK trade documents from email account of former trade minister Liam Fox and leaked them ahead of the general election in order to influence it.
Iranian hacking group Seedworm/MuddyWater hacked into government entities and telecommunications operators in Iraq, Kuwait, Turkey, UAE and Georgia as part of a cyber espionage campaign.

Incident Name: Chinese espionage campaign against japanese organizations
Description: Chinese hacking group Cicada/ APT 10 gained access into network systems and stole credential information from japanese companies in 17 regions and multiple sectors.
The state-sponsored vietnamese hacking group "OceanLotus" created websites for the vietnamese public and Southeast Asia in general to steal information about persons of interest.
APT-C-43 steals Venezuelan military secrets to provide intelligence support for the coup.
The arabic-speaking hacking group MoleRATs/ Gaza Cybergang conducted an espionage campaign on entities and individuals related to the Palestinian Authority.
The Russian government-linked hacking group "Cozy Bear" and an unknown Hacker/ hacking group used the SolarWinds Supply Chain vulnerability to compromise multiple targets worldwide.
The Chinese hacking group "CactusPete" conducted an espionage campaign against the Russian defense industry and the mongolian government.
The pakistani hacking group Transparent Tribe targets military targets in Afghanistan and India.
The hacking group Fishing Elephant targets government and diplomatic entities in Turkey, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Ukraine and China.
Two Chinese hackers working with the Ministry of State Security (MSS) were indicted for unauthorized access and data theft from a variety of victims.
Government-linked Saudi and Emirati hacking groups compromised the mobile devices of Al Jazeera journalists in order to steal information.
The hacking group SectorE02 targets the Pakistani government.
A Hacker steals data of millions of Bulgarians from the National Revenue Agency, a department of the Bulgarian Ministry of Finance.
The Los Angeles Personnel Deparment was hacked and thousands of personal information of police officers were stolen.

The IT networks of three school districts - Sabine, Morehouse, and Ouachita- in North Louisiana were disrupted, some more some less. The governor declared the state of emergency after ransomware attack.
23 local Texas governments have been infected with ransomware.

Incident Name: Fancy Bear hacks US Federal Agency
Description: The Russian state-sponsored hacking group Fancy Bear penetrated the network systems of a yet unknown US Federal Agency and stole data from it.
